comments: Williams (CHA) establishes himself in Poole's (WAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Jones (WAS) grasps and promptly releases Hayward's (CHA) arm as the post entry pass is made. The contact on the play is marginal.
Gafford (WAS) goes into the air to contest the layup attempt and marginal contact occurs with Hayward's (CHA) partially extended off-arm after the release.
Gafford (WAS) firms up over his right leg and marginal contact occurs as Washington (CHA) navigates around the screen.
Poole (WAS) gathers the ball and leaps toward the middle of the floor and Miller (CHA) absorbs the marginal body contact prior to the release of the pass.
Poole's (WAS) off-arm comes down slightly at the beginning of the drive and marginal brush contact occurs with Williams (CHA).
Williams (CHA) turns into Poole (WAS) and delivers body contact after his release on his driving shot attempt, which dislodges him.
Miler (CHA) lowers his hand to Poole's (WAS) back after the release of the driving shot attempt and the contact is marginal.
Washington (CHA) rests and promptly removes his hands from Jones' (WAS) side as he releases away toward the basket and the contact during the pick is marginal.
Miller (CHA) moves alongside Poole's (WAS) path with vertical arms and absorbs the marginal contact as Poole angles back toward the basket.
Ball (CHA) closes out into Jones' (WAS) space and body contact occurs that affects Jones' ability to return to the floor naturally.
Washington (CHA) brings his hand to the ball and incidental hand on ball contact occurs, which legally deflects the ball away from Gafford (WAS) during the rebounding opportunity.
Hayward (CHA) and Shamet (WAS) engage and disengage during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Gafford (WAS) firms up over his right leg and does not deliver illegal contact to Hayward (CHA) when setting the screen.
Hayward (CHA) legally contests Shamet's  (WAS) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Williams (CHA) brings his left arm out as the ball bounces off of the rim and marginal brush contact occurs with Gafford's (WAS) arm.
Williams (CHA) and Shamet (WAS) come together while going into the air and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Washington (CHA) moves alongside Kuzma's (WAS) path and absorbs the marginal contact at the end of the drive.
Washington (CHA) brings his forearm out slightly while bracing for contact with Kuzma (WAS) and the ensuing contact during the floater attempt is marginal.
Kuzma (WAS) returns to the floor and incidental contact occurs with his teammate, Gafford (WAS), which causes Gafford to fall to the floor.
